LIFE_SEAL_INTERPRETATIONS = {
    1: {
        "title": "The Pioneer",
        "summary": "Represents independence, leadership, and the drive to initiate new beginnings. Individuals with this life seal are natural trailblazers, embodying the essence of creation and self-reliance. You are a born leader with an innate ability to see opportunities where others see obstacles, and you possess the courage to forge new paths even when faced with uncertainty.",
        "core_essence": "As a Life Seal 1, you carry the energy of raw creative force and independent thought. You are the spark that ignites movements, the visionary who sees possibilities before they manifest. Your soul resonates with the frequency of initiation, always seeking to break new ground and establish your unique identity in the world. You thrive when you can exercise autonomy and express your original ideas without constraint. Your presence naturally commands attention, and people instinctively look to you for direction during times of uncertainty. This is not merely a personality trait—it is your spiritual blueprint, the divine assignment encoded in your birth date.",
        "strengths": [
            "Exceptional leadership capabilities with natural authority that inspires confidence in others",
            "Innovative thinking that brings fresh perspectives to old problems",
            "Courage to take calculated risks when others hesitate",
            "Strong willpower and determination that pushes through obstacles",
            "Self-motivated and able to work independently without external validation",
            "Quick decision-making ability that seizes opportunities at the right moment",
            "Pioneering spirit that enjoys being first to explore uncharted territory",
            "Natural charisma that attracts followers and supporters to your vision"
        ],
        "challenges": [
            "May become overly dominant or controlling in relationships and team settings",
            "Impatience with slower processes or people who need more time to understand",
            "Difficulty accepting help or delegating tasks, believing you can do it better alone",
            "Tendency toward stubbornness when your ideas are questioned or challenged",
            "Risk of isolation due to preference for solo work over collaboration",
            "Can be perceived as arrogant or self-centered when confidence crosses into pride",
            "May struggle with authority figures who limit your independence",
            "Potential for burnout from taking on too much responsibility alone"
        ],
        "career_guidance": "You excel in positions of leadership and entrepreneurship where you can exercise creative control. Ideal careers include CEO, business owner, entrepreneur, startup founder, creative director, project manager, independent consultant, architect, or any role that allows you to pioneer new initiatives. You thrive in fast-paced environments that reward innovation and quick thinking. Sales leadership, political roles, and military command also align with your natural authority. Avoid positions that require extensive committee work or subordinate roles with little autonomy. You need the freedom to implement your vision without excessive oversight. Consider starting your own business or taking on leadership roles in emerging industries where you can be among the first to establish standards and practices.",
        "relationship_guidance": "In relationships, you need a partner who respects your independence while providing emotional support. You are attracted to strong individuals who can match your intensity without competing for dominance. Communication is crucial—your tendency to make unilateral decisions can create conflict if you don't involve your partner in major choices. Learn to balance your need for autonomy with the intimacy that requires vulnerability and interdependence. You may struggle with emotional expression, preferring action over words, so practice verbalizing your feelings. Your ideal partner appreciates your ambition and gives you space to pursue your goals while maintaining a strong emotional connection. In friendships, you gravitate toward equals who challenge you intellectually. As a parent, teach your children independence while remembering that guidance and patience are equally important. Your greatest relationship growth comes from learning that strength includes the ability to ask for help.",
        "financial_guidance": "Your financial strength lies in your entrepreneurial instincts and willingness to take calculated risks. You have the potential for significant wealth creation through business ventures, innovative investments, or leadership positions with equity compensation. However, your impatience can lead to impulsive financial decisions. Develop a disciplined approach to wealth building by creating long-term strategies alongside your quick wins. You benefit from having a trusted financial advisor who can provide objective counsel when your enthusiasm for a new opportunity clouds your judgment. Multiple income streams suit your pioneering nature—consider investing in startups, real estate, or consulting while maintaining a primary income source. Avoid get-rich-quick schemes that prey on your desire for rapid success. Your financial prosperity grows when you channel your leadership into sustainable ventures rather than chasing every new opportunity. Remember that true wealth requires patience to build foundations even as you pursue innovative growth strategies.",
        "daily_practices": [
            "Morning meditation or quiet reflection to center your energy before taking action",
            "Physical exercise that channels your competitive nature productively (running, martial arts, competitive sports)",
            "Journaling to process emotions you might otherwise suppress",
            "Conscious practice of listening without immediately proposing solutions",
            "Setting aside time for collaborative activities that build team skills",
            "Expressing gratitude to those who support your vision",
            "Regular breaks to prevent burnout from your intense work ethic"
        ],
        "famous_examples": "Life Seal 1 individuals include leaders and innovators such as Tom Hanks (July 9), Ernest Hemingway (July 21), and Hulk Hogan (August 11). These individuals demonstrated the pioneering spirit, leadership, and independent thinking characteristic of Life Seal 1. They carved unique paths in their respective fields, leading with innovation and fearless self-expression.",
        "spiritual_focus": "Emphasizes self-mastery and alignment with divine will, encouraging a life of purpose-driven action and spiritual independence. Your spiritual journey involves learning that true leadership serves others rather than the ego. You are called to pioneer not just for personal glory but to create pathways that benefit humanity. Your challenge is to surrender your will to divine guidance while maintaining the courage to act on inspired ideas. Practice humility by recognizing that your gifts are meant to be used in service to a higher purpose.",
        "bible_verses": "Genesis 1:1 - 'In the beginning God created the heavens and the earth.'; Joshua 1:9 - 'Have I not commanded you? Be strong and courageous. Do not be afraid; do not be discouraged, for the Lord your God will be with you wherever you go.'; Isaiah 43:19 - 'See, I am doing a new thing! Now it springs up; do you not perceive it? I am making a way in the wilderness and streams in the wasteland.'",
        "practical_guidance": ["Focus on balancing independence with collaboration—your greatest achievements will come through empowering teams rather than solo efforts", "Use your leadership to inspire positive change, while cultivating patience and humility in relationships", "Channel your competitive nature into building something lasting rather than winning short-term battles", "Practice vulnerability by sharing your struggles and asking for help when needed", "Mentor others who show leadership potential, multiplying your impact through their success"]
    },
    2: {
        "title": "The Harmonizer",
        "summary": "Symbolizes cooperation, balance, and sensitivity. Those with this life seal are peacemakers, fostering unity and understanding in their interactions. You possess an extraordinary gift for sensing emotional currents and bringing opposing forces into alignment.",
        "core_essence": "As a Life Seal 2, you embody the principle of duality and partnership. Your soul's purpose revolves around creating harmony, facilitating cooperation, and serving as a bridge between different perspectives. You have a refined sensitivity that allows you to perceive subtle energies and emotions that others miss. Your presence naturally calms conflicts and creates safe spaces for authentic connection. Where Life Seal 1 initiates, you refine and balance. Your diplomatic nature is not weakness—it is a sophisticated form of strength that recognizes the power of unity over division. You understand intuitively that lasting solutions come through collaboration rather than domination.",
        "strengths": [
            "Exceptional diplomatic skills with natural ability to mediate disputes",
            "Deep empathy that allows you to understand multiple perspectives simultaneously",
            "Patient listener who creates space for others to express themselves fully",
            "Intuitive understanding of emotional dynamics in relationships and groups",
            "Cooperative spirit that builds consensus and finds win-win solutions",
            "Attention to detail that catches what others overlook",
            "Supportive presence that empowers others to shine",
            "Natural peacemaker who can de-escalate tense situations"
        ],
        "challenges": [
            "Overly sensitive to criticism, taking things personally even when not intended",
            "Indecisiveness stemming from ability to see validity in all viewpoints",
            "Tendency to avoid necessary confrontations to maintain peace at any cost",
            "May become codependent, losing your identity in relationships",
            "Passive-aggressive behavior when unable to express needs directly",
            "Difficulty saying no, leading to over-commitment and resentment",
            "Self-doubt that undermines your valuable contributions",
            "May stay too long in unhealthy relationships hoping to fix them"
        ],
        "career_guidance": "You thrive in roles that require collaboration, diplomacy, and emotional intelligence. Ideal careers include counselor, therapist, mediator, human resources specialist, social worker, diplomat, customer service manager, event coordinator, administrative assistant, or team facilitator. You excel in support roles that keep organizations running smoothly—your attention to detail and people skills make you invaluable. Consider careers in hospitality, healthcare coordination, conflict resolution, or any field requiring negotiation and relationship management. Library science, museum curation, and archival work also suit your careful, methodical nature. Avoid high-pressure competitive environments where collaboration is discouraged. You need workplace cultures that value teamwork and emotional intelligence over individual achievement. Your career satisfaction comes from knowing you've helped create harmony and supported others' success.",
        "relationship_guidance": "In relationships, you are deeply loyal and devoted, often prioritizing your partner's needs above your own. Your challenge is maintaining your identity while in partnership—you can lose yourself trying to accommodate others. Healthy relationships for you involve partners who actively encourage your independence and personal growth. You need to practice asserting your needs and desires rather than always deferring to keep the peace. Your gift for empathy means you attract people who need emotional support, but be cautious of one-sided relationships where you give more than you receive. In friendships, you are the glue that holds groups together, remembering birthdays, checking in on people, and maintaining connections. As a parent, you create nurturing environments but must guard against overprotecting your children. Your greatest relationship growth comes from learning that healthy boundaries strengthen rather than threaten connections. Practice saying no without guilt and expressing disagreement without fear of abandonment.",
        "financial_guidance": "Your financial approach is cautious and collaborative. You prefer financial security over risky ventures and may seek a partner's input on major decisions. This prudence serves you well, though you may miss opportunities by being overly conservative. Build wealth through steady saving, careful budgeting, and long-term investments rather than speculative plays. You benefit from having a financial partner or advisor who complements your careful nature with strategic growth planning. Joint ventures and partnerships can be financially rewarding if you choose reliable collaborators. Avoid making financial decisions solely to please others or maintain harmony—your tendency to defer can lead to poor choices if you trust the wrong people. Develop financial literacy so you can participate equally in money discussions rather than passively accepting others' recommendations. Your financial security grows when you balance your natural caution with calculated growth opportunities and assertively protect your interests in business relationships.",
        "daily_practices": [
            "Morning affirmations that reinforce your worth independent of others' approval",
            "Journaling to identify and express emotions you might otherwise suppress",
            "Setting healthy boundaries practice—saying no to one small request daily",
            "Solitary activities that strengthen your individual identity (solo walks, creative hobbies)",
            "Breathing exercises to center yourself when overwhelmed by others' emotions",
            "Regular check-ins with yourself: 'What do I need right now?'",
            "Practicing direct communication instead of hinting or hoping others guess your needs"
        ],
        "famous_examples": "Life Seal 2 individuals include collaborative leaders such as Bill Clinton (August 19), Amitabh Bachchan (October 11), and Jennifer Aniston (February 11). These figures demonstrate the diplomatic skills, emotional intelligence, and partnership-oriented approach characteristic of Life Seal 2, achieving success through collaboration and relationship building.",
        "spiritual_focus": "Centers on partnership with God and others, highlighting the importance of love, compassion, and service in spiritual growth. Your spiritual path involves learning that true peace begins within—you cannot create external harmony while neglecting your inner needs. You are called to balance service to others with sacred self-care. Your sensitivity is a spiritual gift that allows you to perceive divine presence in relationships and nature. Practice discernment to distinguish between healthy empathy and absorbing others' emotional burdens.",
        "bible_verses": "Ecclesiastes 4:9-10 - 'Two are better than one, because they have a good return for their labor: If either of them falls down, one can help the other up.'; Matthew 5:9 - 'Blessed are the peacemakers, for they will be called children of God.'; Romans 12:18 - 'If it is possible, as far as it depends on you, live at peace with everyone.'",
        "practical_guidance": ["Embrace your role as a bridge-builder while maintaining your individual identity", "Practice assertiveness to avoid being overshadowed—your voice matters as much as others'", "Seek environments where your nurturing nature can flourish without being exploited", "Learn that healthy conflict can strengthen relationships rather than destroy them", "Develop decision-making confidence by starting with small choices and building up"]
    },
    3: {
        "title": "The Communicator",
        "summary": "Embodies creativity, expression, and joy. This life seal signifies individuals who bring light and inspiration through their words and actions. You are the spark of enthusiasm that ignites rooms and the creative force that transforms ordinary moments into memorable experiences.",
        "core_essence": "As a Life Seal 3, you carry the vibration of creative expression and joyful communication. Your soul purpose involves bringing beauty, laughter, and inspiration into the world through your words, art, or presence. You have a natural gift for seeing the positive potential in situations and people, and your enthusiasm is genuinely contagious. You are meant to create, whether through traditional arts, verbal expression, fashion, design, or simply the art of living with vibrant authenticity. Your energy lifts others out of darkness and reminds them that life is meant to be celebrated. This is not superficiality—it is a profound spiritual service that counterbalances the world's heaviness with lightness and hope.",
        "strengths": [
            "Exceptional communication skills across multiple mediums (writing, speaking, visual arts)",
            "Natural optimism that finds silver linings and opportunities in challenges",
            "Social charisma that draws people and creates instant connections",
            "Creative problem-solving that thinks outside conventional boundaries",
            "Entertaining presence that makes gatherings memorable and enjoyable",
            "Versatility to adapt your expression to different audiences and contexts",
            "Genuine enthusiasm that motivates and inspires others to action",
            "Ability to articulate complex ideas in accessible, engaging ways"
        ],
        "challenges": [
            "Scattered energy that starts many projects but struggles to complete them",
            "Superficiality when you skim surfaces rather than develop depth",
            "Prioritizing fun and social activities over responsibilities and commitments",
            "Difficulty with routine tasks and structured environments",
            "May use humor or charm to avoid dealing with serious emotions or issues",
            "Tendency to overpromise and underdeliver when enthusiasm exceeds capacity",
            "Can be perceived as attention-seeking or insincere",
            "Financial instability from impulsive spending on experiences and aesthetics"
        ],
        "career_guidance": "You flourish in careers that combine creativity with communication. Ideal roles include writer, public speaker, actor, comedian, marketing professional, social media manager, graphic designer, advertising creative, event planner, teacher, journalist, or entertainer. You excel in environments that value innovation and allow flexible expression of your ideas. Consider careers in media, arts, entertainment, public relations, or content creation. Sales roles suit you if you believe in the product—your genuine enthusiasm is your greatest asset. Avoid monotonous desk jobs with rigid structures and limited creative input. You need variety, social interaction, and opportunities to showcase your creative talents. Entrepreneurship can work if you partner with detail-oriented people who handle operations while you focus on vision and marketing. Your career satisfaction comes from work that allows authentic self-expression and makes a positive emotional impact on others.",
        "relationship_guidance": "In relationships, you are romantic, expressive, and fun-loving. You bring joy and spontaneity to partnerships, always finding new ways to celebrate love. Your challenge is maintaining depth when things become routine or difficult. You may avoid serious conversations about problems, preferring to keep things light. Healthy relationships for you require partners who appreciate your playful nature while gently encouraging emotional depth and commitment. You need someone who enjoys social activities but also values intimate one-on-one connection. Be mindful of your tendency to flirt harmlessly—what you see as friendly charm may threaten insecure partners. In friendships, you are the life of the party but may have many acquaintances and few deep connections. Work on being present during difficult times, not just fun ones. As a parent, you create joyful, creative home environments but must balance this with necessary structure and discipline. Your greatest relationship growth comes from learning that true intimacy includes sharing your struggles, not just your highlights.",
        "financial_guidance": "Your financial challenge is balancing your desire for beautiful experiences with practical money management. You can be impulsive with spending, especially on social activities, creative supplies, fashion, or entertainment. Your income potential is high due to your communication skills and creativity, but inconsistent cash flow is common if you work in creative fields. Build financial stability by creating separate accounts—one for creative spending and one for necessities and savings. You benefit from automatic savings plans that remove money before you see it. Consider income streams that reward your communication skills—freelance writing, speaking engagements, online content creation, or teaching. Avoid get-rich-quick schemes that promise easy money for minimal work. Your financial prosperity grows when you treat your creative talents as legitimate business assets requiring professional management. Partner with or hire someone to handle the financial details you find tedious. Invest in experiences and education that expand your skills, but always maintain an emergency fund for practical security.",
        "daily_practices": [
            "Morning creative expression before checking devices (journaling, sketching, dancing)",
            "Completing one small task fully before starting the next to build follow-through muscles",
            "Scheduled 'free time' for spontaneous creativity within structured days",
            "Gratitude practice that deepens your natural optimism with intentional reflection",
            "Regular physical exercise that channels your high energy productively",
            "End-of-day review: celebrate what you completed, not just what you started",
            "One-on-one deep conversation weekly to balance your social breadth with depth"
        ],
        "famous_examples": "Life Seal 3 individuals include creative communicators such as Christina Aguilera (December 18), Snoop Dogg (October 20), and Brendan Fraser (December 3). These artists demonstrate the expressive creativity, communication mastery, and joyful presence characteristic of Life Seal 3, using their platforms to entertain and inspire.",
        "spiritual_focus": "Focuses on expressing divine joy and creativity, encouraging a life that glorifies God through artistic and communicative gifts. Your spiritual path involves recognizing that your creative expression is a form of worship and service. You are called to use your gifts not just for personal enjoyment but to heal, inspire, and uplift others. Your challenge is developing the discipline to fully manifest your creative visions rather than scattering your energy across too many interests. Practice finishing what you start as a spiritual discipline.",
        "bible_verses": "Proverbs 17:22 - 'A cheerful heart is good medicine, but a crushed spirit dries up the bones.'; Psalm 33:3 - 'Sing to him a new song; play skillfully, and shout for joy.'; Colossians 3:23 - 'Whatever you do, work at it with all your heart, as working for the Lord, not for human masters.'",
        "practical_guidance": ["Channel your creativity into meaningful projects by choosing quality over quantity", "Balance spontaneity with discipline to achieve lasting impact—finish what you start", "Develop depth in relationships by being present during difficult moments, not just celebrations", "Create systems that handle practical responsibilities so your creative energy stays free", "Use your communication gifts to add genuine value, not just entertain"]
    },
    4: {
        "title": "The Builder",
        "summary": "Represents stability, hard work, and practicality. Those with this life seal are foundation-layers, committed to building enduring structures in life. You are the bedrock upon which lasting success is constructed, embodying the principles of discipline, reliability, and methodical progress.",
        "core_essence": "As a Life Seal 4, you carry the energy of structure, order, and manifestation in the physical realm. Your soul's purpose involves creating stability and building foundations that will endure for generations. You understand instinctively that nothing worthwhile comes easily—true achievement requires patience, planning, and persistent effort. You value tradition, systems, and proven methods while also possessing the practical wisdom to adapt when necessary. Your presence brings a sense of security to chaotic situations. Where others see overwhelming tasks, you see step-by-step processes that can be completed through steady application of effort. You are the architect of the material world, transforming abstract visions into concrete reality through dedicated work.",
        "strengths": [
            "Exceptional organizational skills that create order from chaos",
            "Reliability that makes you the person everyone counts on",
            "Strong work ethic that perseveres through difficulties without complaint",
            "Practical problem-solving grounded in real-world constraints",
            "Attention to detail that ensures quality and thoroughness",
            "Financial prudence and resource management skills",
            "Ability to create and follow systematic processes",
            "Patience to see long-term projects through to completion"
        ],
        "challenges": [
            "Rigidity that resists change even when adaptation would be beneficial",
            "Workaholism that sacrifices relationships and health for productivity",
            "Excessive focus on material security at the expense of emotional or spiritual needs",
            "Difficulty expressing emotions or appearing vulnerable",
            "Tendency to become controlling when others don't meet your standards",
            "May view rest or play as wasteful rather than necessary",
            "Stubbornness about 'the right way' to do things",
            "Can be overly critical of yourself and others when perfection isn't achieved"
        ],
        "career_guidance": "You excel in careers that require precision, systematic thinking, and long-term planning. Ideal roles include project manager, engineer, accountant, architect, contractor, financial analyst, operations manager, quality assurance specialist, database administrator, or urban planner. You thrive in industries with clear structures and measurable outcomes—construction, manufacturing, finance, government, or established corporations. Your ability to create and maintain systems makes you invaluable in roles requiring process improvement and organizational efficiency. Consider careers in logistics, supply chain management, compliance, or any field requiring meticulous record-keeping and attention to regulations. Avoid chaotic startup environments or highly creative roles with minimal structure. You need clear expectations, defined processes, and tangible results you can measure. Your career satisfaction comes from building something lasting and seeing the concrete results of your dedicated effort.",
        "relationship_guidance": "In relationships, you are steadfastly loyal and committed for the long haul. You show love through practical actions—fixing things, managing finances, ensuring stability—rather than romantic gestures or verbal expressions. Your challenge is learning that emotional intimacy requires vulnerability, not just practical support. Partners may crave more spontaneity, affection, and emotional availability than you naturally provide. Make conscious efforts to express feelings verbally and engage in activities that aren't productive but simply enjoyable. You need partners who appreciate your stability and don't mistake your reserved nature for lack of caring. Be mindful of trying to control loved ones through rigid rules or expectations. In friendships, you are dependable but may have a small circle due to your high standards and limited social time. As a parent, you provide security and teach valuable life skills, but remember to balance structure with warmth and flexibility. Your greatest relationship growth comes from learning that love includes accepting imperfection in yourself and others.",
        "financial_guidance": "Your financial approach is conservative, disciplined, and focused on long-term security. You are naturally skilled at budgeting, saving, and building wealth through patient accumulation. This prudence serves you well, though you may be overly risk-averse, missing growth opportunities through excessive caution. Build wealth through real estate, index funds, bonds, and other stable investments that provide steady returns. You excel at creating multiple income streams through systematic side projects. Avoid speculative investments and get-rich-quick schemes—your wealth-building strength is consistency, not timing markets. You benefit from occasionally consulting with advisors who can encourage calculated growth moves when appropriate. Don't let fear of financial insecurity drive you to work yourself to exhaustion. Money is meant to provide security and freedom, not just accumulate. Practice spending on experiences and quality of life improvements without guilt. Your financial prosperity grows when you balance your natural frugality with strategic investments and intentional enjoyment of the wealth you create.",
        "daily_practices": [
            "Morning routine that includes planning but also intentional breaks for flexibility",
            "Physical labor or exercise to ground your energy in your body",
            "Scheduled downtime where productivity is not the goal—rest is productive",
            "Expressing one feeling daily to practice emotional vulnerability",
            "Random acts of spontaneity to loosen rigid patterns (take different route, try new food)",
            "End-of-day gratitude for what you accomplished and what you let go",
            "Weekly creative activity with no practical purpose—just for enjoyment"
        ],
        "famous_examples": "Life Seal 4 individuals include dedicated builders such as Bill Gates (October 28), Oprah Winfrey (January 29), and Clint Eastwood (May 31). These figures demonstrate the disciplined work ethic, systematic thinking, and foundation-building characteristic of Life Seal 4, creating enduring legacies through patient, persistent effort.",
        "spiritual_focus": "Emphasizes faithfulness and stewardship, aligning with God's call to build His kingdom through diligent service. Your spiritual path involves learning that true security comes from faith, not just material preparation. You are called to build not just physical structures but also spiritual foundations in your community. Your challenge is trusting divine timing rather than trying to control everything through excessive planning. Practice surrendering to grace while maintaining your disciplined approach to spiritual growth.",
        "bible_verses": "Proverbs 10:4 - 'Lazy hands make for poverty, but diligent hands bring wealth.'; Matthew 7:24-25 - 'Therefore everyone who hears these words of mine and puts them into practice is like a wise man who built his house on the rock.'; Colossians 3:23 - 'Whatever you do, work at it with all your heart, as working for the Lord, not for human masters.'",
        "practical_guidance": ["Value hard work but remember that rest is equally important for sustainable success", "Use your stability to support others while remaining open to flexibility and new approaches", "Express emotions verbally, not just through practical actions", "Allow yourself and others to be imperfect—progress matters more than perfection", "Invest your resources not just in material security but also in relationships and experiences that enrich life"]
    },
    5: {
        "title": "The Adventurer",
        "summary": "Symbolizes freedom, versatility, and change. Individuals with this life seal are seekers of experience, embracing life's variety and challenges. You are the embodiment of dynamic energy, constantly exploring new horizons and refusing to be confined by convention.",
        "core_essence": "As a Life Seal 5, you carry the vibration of freedom, change, and experiential learning. Your soul purpose involves exploring the full spectrum of human experience and sharing the wisdom gained from your adventures. You are naturally curious about everything and everyone, possessing an insatiable appetite for new experiences, cultures, ideas, and sensations. You understand that life is meant to be lived fully, not just observed from safety. Your presence brings excitement and fresh perspective to stagnant situations. You are the catalyst for necessary change, the one who questions limiting traditions and expands possibilities for yourself and others. Freedom is not selfishness for you—it is your spiritual requirement for growth and contribution.",
        "strengths": [
            "Exceptional adaptability that thrives in changing circumstances",
            "Quick thinking that responds effectively to unexpected situations",
            "Diverse skill set from broad range of experiences and interests",
            "Natural sales ability and persuasive communication",
            "Courage to take risks that others fear",
            "Ability to connect with people from all walks of life",
            "Resourcefulness that finds creative solutions with limited resources",
            "Infectious enthusiasm that inspires others to step out of comfort zones"
        ],
        "challenges": [
            "Restlessness that prevents deep commitment to people, places, or projects",
            "Impulsiveness that leads to decisions without considering long-term consequences",
            "Difficulty with routine, structure, or repetitive tasks",
            "May avoid responsibility to maintain freedom",
            "Tendency toward excess—overindulgence in food, substances, or experiences",
            "Unreliability when confined by commitments or expectations",
            "May run from problems rather than working through them",
            "Can be scattered, starting many things but mastering few"
        ],
        "career_guidance": "You excel in careers offering variety, travel, and autonomy. Ideal roles include travel writer, photographer, sales representative, tour guide, flight attendant, event promoter, freelance consultant, digital nomad, entrepreneur, journalist, or adventure guide. You thrive in fast-paced environments with constantly changing challenges. Consider careers in hospitality, tourism, international business, emergency services, or any field that prevents monotony. Your versatility makes you valuable in roles requiring quick adaptation and diverse skills. Avoid traditional 9-to-5 desk jobs with rigid structures and predictable routines. You need freedom to manage your own schedule and vary your activities. Multiple income streams from diverse projects suit your nature better than single-track careers. Your career satisfaction comes from work that provides new experiences, meets new people, and allows geographic and intellectual exploration.",
        "relationship_guidance": "In relationships, you are exciting, adventurous, and fun but can struggle with the consistency and commitment that intimacy requires. You fear being trapped or losing your freedom, which can manifest as avoiding deep commitment or running when relationships become routine. Healthy relationships for you require partners who are equally adventurous or at least supportive of your need for variety and independence. You need someone who understands that your desire for freedom isn't rejection—it's how you maintain your sense of self. Be honest about your needs rather than promising commitment you can't sustain. In friendships, you have connections worldwide but may lack deep roots anywhere. Work on being present and reliable for those who matter most. As a parent, you teach children to be bold and curious, but must balance this with necessary structure and stability. Your greatest relationship growth comes from learning that commitment can be liberating rather than limiting when chosen consciously.",
        "financial_guidance": "Your financial pattern tends toward feast or famine—periods of abundance followed by scarcity. Your versatility creates income opportunities, but impulsiveness and love of experience can lead to overspending. You may invest in travel, courses, and adventures while neglecting emergency savings. Build financial stability by creating automated savings that protect you from your own spontaneity. You benefit from liquid investments that don't lock up your money long-term. Consider income streams that leverage your diverse experiences—consulting, speaking, writing, or creating online courses. Your ability to sell and connect with people is a major financial asset if channeled professionally. Avoid gambling or high-risk speculation—your natural risk-taking should be strategic, not reckless. Your financial prosperity grows when you balance your need for freedom with basic financial responsibility. Have enough structure to ensure security, then spend freely on experiences that enrich your life and expand your possibilities.",
        "daily_practices": [
            "Morning movement practice that varies daily (running, yoga, dancing)",
            "One consistent habit maintained daily to build follow-through muscles",
            "Evening reflection: What new thing did I experience today?",
            "Weekly check-in on commitments to ensure you're honoring promises",
            "Learning something new regularly to satisfy curiosity productively",
            "Grounding practice (meditation, nature) to balance your high energy",
            "Scheduled adventure time within responsible life structure"
        ],
        "famous_examples": "Life Seal 5 individuals include adventurous spirits such as Angelina Jolie (June 4), Steven Spielberg (December 18), and Beyoncé (September 4). These figures demonstrate the versatile creativity, fearless exploration, and dynamic energy characteristic of Life Seal 5, constantly reinventing themselves and refusing to be confined.",
        "spiritual_focus": "Highlights the journey of faith, encouraging exploration of God's diverse creation and personal spiritual freedom. Your spiritual path involves learning that true freedom comes from discipline, not lack of structure. You are called to explore not just the physical world but also inner spiritual territories. Your challenge is developing enough consistency in practice to experience transformation that requires time and commitment. Practice viewing spiritual discipline as an adventure rather than confinement.",
        "bible_verses": "Jeremiah 29:11 - 'For I know the plans I have for you,' declares the Lord, 'plans to prosper you and not to harm you, plans to give you hope and a future.'; Philippians 4:13 - 'I can do all things through Christ who strengthens me.'; Galatians 5:13 - 'You, my brothers and sisters, were called to be free. But do not use your freedom to indulge the flesh; rather, serve one another humbly in love.'",
        "practical_guidance": ["Embrace change as growth while maintaining core commitments to people and values", "Cultivate discipline to harness your versatility for meaningful impact", "Choose freedom with responsibility—true liberty requires honoring your word", "Channel restlessness into strategic exploration rather than aimless wandering", "Build a life structure flexible enough to satisfy your need for variety while providing stability"]
    },
    6: {
        "title": "The Nurturer",
        "summary": "Embodies responsibility, love, and service. This life seal signifies caregivers who prioritize the well-being of others and family harmony. You are the heart that holds communities together, embodying unconditional love and selfless service.",
        "core_essence": "As a Life Seal 6, you carry the energy of unconditional love, responsibility, and service. Your soul purpose revolves around creating harmony, beauty, and healing in your environment and relationships. You have an innate ability to sense what others need and a genuine desire to provide it. Your presence creates safe spaces where people feel seen, valued, and nurtured. You are drawn to teaching, healing, counseling, and any role that supports others' growth and well-being. Home and family are sacred to you, and you invest tremendous energy in creating environments where loved ones can flourish. Your love is expressed through action—cooking, cleaning, organizing, supporting—not just words. This is your divine assignment: to embody love in tangible, practical forms.",
        "strengths": [
            "Deep compassion that genuinely cares about others' well-being",
            "Strong sense of responsibility that follows through on commitments",
            "Natural counseling ability that helps others solve problems",
            "Creates beautiful, harmonious environments",
            "Exceptional listening skills that make people feel truly heard",
            "Loyalty and dependability in all relationships",
            "Teaching ability that patiently guides others to understanding",
            "Service-oriented mindset that finds fulfillment in helping others"
        ],
        "challenges": [
            "Overly sacrificial, neglecting your own needs to serve others",
            "May become controlling or interfering, believing you know what's best",
            "Difficulty accepting help or admitting vulnerability",
            "Can be judgmental when others don't meet your standards of behavior",
            "Martyr complex that breeds resentment when service isn't appreciated",
            "Codependency in relationships, enabling unhealthy behaviors",
            "May use guilt or manipulation to maintain family harmony",
            "Perfectionism about how things 'should' be done"
        ],
        "career_guidance": "You excel in service-oriented careers where you can directly impact others' lives. Ideal roles include teacher, nurse, counselor, therapist, social worker, home care provider, interior designer, chef, nutritionist, child development specialist, or community organizer. You thrive in healing professions and anywhere you can nurture growth and well-being. Consider careers in healthcare, education, hospitality, family services, or non-profit organizations. Your ability to create beauty makes you valuable in fields like floral design, home staging, or aesthetic services. Avoid cutthroat competitive environments or roles requiring emotional detachment. You need work that aligns with your values and allows you to see the positive impact of your service. Your career satisfaction comes from knowing you've made others' lives better, easier, or more beautiful.",
        "relationship_guidance": "In relationships, you are devoted, loyal, and deeply committed to your loved ones' happiness. Your challenge is maintaining healthy boundaries and not losing yourself in service to others. You may attract people who take advantage of your generous nature or become dependent on your caretaking. Healthy relationships require partners who reciprocate your care and actively prevent you from over-functioning. You need someone who insists you prioritize your own needs and models healthy self-care. Practice receiving love, not just giving it. Learn to distinguish between helping and enabling—true love sometimes requires allowing others to face consequences of their choices. In friendships, you are the one everyone calls in crisis, which can be exhausting. As a parent, you are naturally nurturing but must guard against over-protecting or controlling your children. Your greatest relationship growth comes from learning that self-care is not selfish—you cannot pour from an empty cup.",
        "financial_guidance": "Your financial challenge is valuing your service appropriately. You may undercharge for your work or give away your time and resources too freely. You need to understand that receiving fair compensation for your gifts is not selfish—it ensures you can sustain your service long-term. Build wealth by establishing clear rates for your professional services and sticking to them. You benefit from creating businesses around your natural caregiving abilities—consulting, coaching, design services, or product creation. Avoid financial codependency where you enable others' irresponsibility by repeatedly bailing them out. Teach financial literacy to those you care for rather than creating dependency. Your prosperity grows when you balance generous giving with wise stewardship. Invest in creating beautiful, comfortable home environments that replenish your energy. Practice receiving abundantly, trusting that you deserve prosperity for the tremendous value you provide.",
        "daily_practices": [
            "Morning self-care ritual before serving others (bath, meditation, favorite beverage)",
            "Saying no to one request daily to build boundary muscles",
            "Identifying and expressing one personal need without apologizing",
            "Creating beauty in your environment for your own enjoyment",
            "Receiving compliments and help without deflecting or minimizing",
            "Evening reflection: Did I care for myself as well as others today?",
            "Weekly activity purely for your pleasure, not anyone else's benefit"
        ],
        "famous_examples": "Life Seal 6 individuals include devoted nurturers such as Mother Teresa (August 26), Eleanor Roosevelt (October 11), and Warren Buffett (August 30). These figures demonstrate the service-oriented nature, responsibility, and commitment to others' well-being characteristic of Life Seal 6, using their gifts to improve countless lives.",
        "spiritual_focus": "Centers on selfless love and service, mirroring Christ's example of sacrificial giving. Your spiritual path involves learning that healthy service flows from fullness, not depletion. You are called to serve from overflow, not emptiness. Your challenge is receiving divine love as freely as you give it, trusting that you are worthy of care simply for existing, not just for what you do for others. Practice viewing self-care as spiritual discipline that sustains your ministry of service.",
        "bible_verses": "1 Corinthians 13:6-7 - 'Love does not delight in evil but rejoices with the truth. It always protects, always trusts, always hopes, always perseveres.'; Galatians 5:13 - 'You, my brothers and sisters, were called to be free. But do not use your freedom to indulge the flesh; rather, serve one another humbly in love.'; Matthew 11:28 - 'Come to me, all you who are weary and burdened, and I will give you rest.'",
        "practical_guidance": ["Balance caregiving with self-care—you matter as much as those you serve", "Use your nurturing spirit to foster healthy independence, not dependency", "Set clear boundaries about what you will and won't do for others", "Charge appropriately for your professional services—your gifts have value", "Learn to receive care, help, and love as graciously as you give it"]
    },
    7: {
        "title": "The Seeker",
        "summary": "Represents introspection, wisdom, and spirituality. Those with this life seal are deep thinkers, pursuing knowledge and inner truth. You are the philosopher and mystic, diving beneath surface appearances to discover hidden wisdom and universal truths.",
        "core_essence": "As a Life Seal 7, you carry the vibration of spiritual seeking, analytical mastery, and inner wisdom. Your soul purpose involves the pursuit of truth, whether through science, spirituality, philosophy, or research. You are naturally drawn to the mysteries of existence, asking questions others don't think to ask. Solitude is not loneliness for you—it is the necessary condition for deep contemplation and connection with higher consciousness. You see through superficiality and crave authentic understanding. Your presence brings depth to shallow conversations and insight to complex problems. You are here to bridge the material and spiritual realms, translating profound truths into accessible wisdom for others. Your mind is a sacred gift meant to illuminate darkness with the light of understanding.",
        "strengths": [
            "Exceptional analytical ability that sees patterns others miss",
            "Deep intuition that accesses wisdom beyond logical reasoning",
            "Intellectual integrity that seeks truth over comfortable beliefs",
            "Natural research skills that pursue knowledge systematically",
            "Ability to work independently without need for external validation",
            "Spiritual depth that connects with transcendent realities",
            "Discernment that distinguishes genuine from false",
            "Teaching ability that shares complex concepts with clarity"
        ],
        "challenges": [
            "Tendency toward isolation that limits human connection",
            "Over-intellectualization that avoids feeling emotions",
            "May be overly critical or skeptical, dismissing what can't be proven",
            "Difficulty with small talk and superficial social interactions",
            "Can appear cold or aloof when deep in thought",
            "Analysis paralysis preventing action while seeking perfect understanding",
            "May struggle with practical matters while focused on abstract concepts",
            "Superiority complex based on intellectual achievement"
        ],
        "career_guidance": "You excel in careers requiring deep analysis, research, and specialized expertise. Ideal roles include researcher, scientist, professor, data analyst, philosopher, spiritual teacher, psychologist, technical writer, software engineer, or forensic investigator. You thrive in academic environments, think tanks, R&D departments, or any setting valuing expertise over social skills. Consider careers in theology, archaeology, astronomy, quantum physics, or any field exploring profound questions. Library science, archival work, and information management suit your love of organized knowledge. Avoid careers requiring constant social interaction or sales-focused roles. You need intellectual challenges, time for deep focus, and appreciation for your specialized knowledge. Your career satisfaction comes from contributing to collective understanding and solving complex problems that others can't.",
        "relationship_guidance": "In relationships, you are deeply loyal but may struggle with emotional expression and vulnerability. You show love through understanding and thoughtful analysis of your partner's needs, but may miss the emotional warmth they crave. Your challenge is balancing your need for solitude with the intimacy requirements of close relationships. Healthy relationships for you require partners who respect your need for alone time and intellectual depth. You need someone who engages you mentally while gently drawing out your emotional side. Practice sharing your inner world verbally, not just assuming your partner understands your thoughts. In friendships, you have few but deep connections with fellow thinkers. As a parent, you encourage intellectual development but must remember to show physical affection and emotional validation. Your greatest relationship growth comes from learning that intellectual connection isn't a substitute for emotional intimacy—both are necessary.",
        "financial_guidance": "Your financial approach is thoughtful and analytical. You research investments thoroughly and make careful decisions based on data rather than emotion. This serves you well for long-term wealth building through strategic, informed choices. Your challenge is that perfectionism in research can lead to missing time-sensitive opportunities. Build wealth through expertise-based income—consulting, teaching, writing, or specialized services that command premium rates. Your deep knowledge in niche areas can be extremely profitable if marketed properly. Avoid impulsive spending, which isn't your tendency, but also avoid excessive frugality driven by fear. You benefit from systematic investment plans that remove emotion from the equation. Consider passive income from intellectual property—books, courses, patents, or proprietary research. Your financial prosperity grows when you monetize your expertise appropriately and invest with the same analytical rigor you apply to other areas. Trust your research, make decisions, and allow time for compound growth.",
        "daily_practices": [
            "Morning meditation or contemplative practice to center your energy",
            "Journaling to externalize insights and track intellectual growth",
            "Dedicated study time for pursuing current knowledge interests",
            "Physical exercise to ground spiritual energy in your body",
            "One social interaction daily to maintain human connection",
            "Nature time to balance intellectual activity with present-moment awareness",
            "Evening gratitude practice for both intellectual and emotional blessings"
        ],
        "famous_examples": "Life Seal 7 individuals include deep thinkers such as Stephen Hawking (January 8), Princess Diana (July 1), and Elon Musk (June 28). These figures demonstrate the analytical brilliance, spiritual depth, and quest for truth characteristic of Life Seal 7, using their profound understanding to benefit humanity.",
        "spiritual_focus": "Emphasizes deep communion with God, encouraging prayer, meditation, and pursuit of divine wisdom. Your spiritual path involves balancing intellectual understanding with mystical experience—truth is both rational and transcendent. You are called to share your spiritual insights, not hoard them in isolation. Your challenge is trusting intuitive knowing as much as logical proof. Practice faith as a complement to understanding, recognizing that some truths exceed mental comprehension.",
        "bible_verses": "James 1:5 - 'If any of you lacks wisdom, you should ask God, who gives generously to all without finding fault, and it will be given to you.'; Proverbs 2:6 - 'For the Lord gives wisdom; from his mouth come knowledge and understanding.'; Psalm 46:10 - 'Be still, and know that I am God.'",
        "practical_guidance": ["Share your insights with others rather than hoarding knowledge in isolation", "Balance introspection with action—wisdom unused doesn't serve the world", "Practice emotional vulnerability as rigorously as intellectual honesty", "Value experiential knowing alongside analytical understanding", "Use your analytical gifts to illuminate truth while remaining humble about the mysteries you cannot solve"]
    },
    8: {
        "title": "The Achiever",
        "summary": "Symbolizes power, abundance, and material success. Individuals with this life seal are driven to achieve goals and manifest prosperity. You are the master of the material realm, capable of transforming vision into tangible wealth and influential accomplishment.",
        "core_essence": "As a Life Seal 8, you carry the vibration of manifestation, power, and material mastery. Your soul purpose involves demonstrating how spiritual principles can create abundance in the physical world. You have an innate understanding of systems, hierarchies, and the mechanics of success. You are naturally drawn to positions of authority and influence, not from ego but from genuine capacity to lead organizations and create wealth. Your presence commands respect, and people instinctively recognize your executive abilities. You understand that money and power are neutral tools that amplify the values of those who wield them. You are here to build prosperity not just for yourself but as a demonstration of divine abundance available to all. Your success is meant to inspire and create opportunities for others.",
        "strengths": ["Exceptional business acumen and strategic thinking", "Natural leadership in corporate and organizational settings", "Financial intelligence that understands money dynamics", "Ability to see the big picture while managing complex details", "Persistence that overcomes obstacles through sheer determination", "Courage to make bold decisions that others fear", "Organizational skills that create efficient, profitable systems", "Authority and executive presence that inspires confidence"],
        "challenges": ["May prioritize material success over relationships and spiritual growth", "Workaholic tendencies that sacrifice health and personal life", "Can become ruthless in pursuit of goals, damaging relationships", "Difficulty delegating or trusting others with important tasks", "May equate self-worth with net worth and professional achievement", "Tendency to control situations and people", "Can be intimidating or domineering without realizing it", "Risk of ethical compromise when success is the primary focus"],
        "career_guidance": "You excel in executive leadership, entrepreneurship, and any role involving financial management and strategic planning. Ideal careers include CEO, CFO, investment banker, corporate executive, business owner, real estate developer, attorney, financial advisor, or venture capitalist. You thrive in competitive environments where performance is rewarded handsomely. Consider roles in mergers and acquisitions, private equity, corporate law, or high-level consulting. Your ability to see opportunities and mobilize resources makes you valuable in turnaround situations and growth ventures. Avoid subordinate roles that don't utilize your leadership capacity. You need authority, significant responsibility, and compensation that reflects your contribution. Your career satisfaction comes from measurable achievement, building successful enterprises, and creating wealth that provides security and opportunities for yourself and others.",
        "relationship_guidance": "In relationships, you are generous provider and loyal partner, but may struggle with vulnerability and work-life balance. You show love through financial provision and problem-solving but may miss the emotional intimacy your partner craves. Your challenge is remembering that relationships require time and emotional presence, not just material provision. Healthy relationships require partners who respect your ambition while insisting you prioritize the relationship. You need someone strong enough to call out your workaholic tendencies without being intimidated by your success. Practice being present when home rather than mentally solving business problems. In friendships, be mindful that not everyone operates at your intensity level or shares your focus on achievement. As a parent, teach your children about success while demonstrating that their worth isn't tied to their accomplishments. Your greatest relationship growth comes from learning that love, connection, and presence are achievements that matter as much as professional success.",
        "financial_guidance": "Your financial strength is obvious—you have natural money-making ability and understand wealth creation intuitively. You think in terms of systems, leverage, and scalability rather than trading time for money. Build wealth through business ownership, real estate, strategic investments, and opportunities that create passive income streams. You have the risk tolerance and strategic thinking to build significant wealth if you maintain ethical standards. Your challenge is knowing when enough is enough—endless pursuit of more can prevent enjoying what you've already built. Avoid measuring success only in financial terms, which can lead to ethical compromises or neglecting other life areas. You benefit from philanthropic giving that fulfills your soul while creating tax advantages. Use wealth to create positive impact, not just accumulate zeros in accounts. Your financial prosperity grows when you align money-making with purpose and use success to bless others generously. Remember that you can't take it with you—build legacy through impact, not just accumulation.",
        "daily_practices": ["Morning visualization of success in all life areas, not just business", "Physical exercise to release stress and maintain health for long-term success", "Daily quality time with loved ones with devices off", "Evening reflection: Did I live my values today or just pursue goals?", "Regular acts of generosity to keep money flowing and maintain perspective", "Meditation or spiritual practice to remember that you are more than your achievements", "Weekly digital detox where work is completely off-limits"],
        "famous_examples": "Life Seal 8 individuals include powerful achievers such as Pablo Picasso (October 25), Nelson Mandela (July 18), and Matt Damon (October 8). These figures demonstrate the material mastery, leadership ability, and influential impact characteristic of Life Seal 8, using their power and resources to create lasting change.",
        "spiritual_focus": "Focuses on stewardship of resources, aligning personal success with God's purposes for generosity and justice. Your spiritual path involves learning that true power comes from service, not domination. You are called to be a steward, not just an accumulator—a channel for abundance, not a dam that hoards it. Your challenge is remembering that worldly success is temporary while spiritual development is eternal. Practice tithing and generosity as spiritual disciplines that prevent money from becoming your god.",
        "bible_verses": "Proverbs 10:22 - 'The blessing of the Lord makes rich, and he adds no sorrow with it.'; Luke 12:15 - 'Then he said to them, 'Watch out! Be on your guard against all kinds of greed; life does not consist in an abundance of things.'; Matthew 6:24 - 'No one can serve two masters. Either you will hate the one and love the other, or you will be devoted to the one and despise the other. You cannot serve both God and money.'",
        "practical_guidance": ["Pursue success ethically—shortcuts that compromise integrity will eventually cost you everything", "Use achievements to bless others rather than just elevating yourself", "Maintain balance between material and spiritual wealth—both are important", "Build legacy through impact and relationships, not just financial accumulation", "Practice present-moment awareness in personal relationships, giving them the same focus you give business"]
    },
    9: {
        "title": "The Humanitarian",
        "summary": "Embodies compassion, idealism, and global awareness. This life seal signifies visionaries who work for the greater good of humanity. You are the bridge between what is and what could be, holding space for humanity's highest potential while working tirelessly to manifest it.",
        "core_essence": "As a Life Seal 9, you carry the vibration of universal love, completion, and global consciousness. Your soul purpose involves serving humanity's evolution, whether through arts, activism, healing, or any work that elevates collective consciousness. You feel deeply connected to all of humanity, experiencing others' suffering as your own and celebrating their joy with genuine delight. You are naturally drawn to causes larger than yourself, seeing individual problems as symptoms of systemic issues requiring comprehensive solutions. Your presence brings compassion and perspective to difficult situations. You understand that we are all interconnected, and that healing anywhere contributes to healing everywhere. You are here to be a light-bearer, showing others what's possible when we lead with love rather than fear.",
        "strengths": ["Deep compassion for all beings regardless of background or circumstance", "Visionary thinking that sees possibilities for transformation", "Artistic and creative abilities that inspire and heal", "Global perspective that transcends narrow self-interest", "Charismatic presence that attracts people to worthy causes", "Ability to see the divine in everyone and everything", "Natural teaching and mentoring abilities", "Courage to champion unpopular but necessary truths"],
        "challenges": ["Overly idealistic expectations that lead to disappointment", "Emotional intensity that can overwhelm both yourself and others", "Tendency to take on the world's problems as personal responsibility", "May neglect practical details in pursuit of grand visions", "Burnout from giving too much without adequate self-care", "Can be judgmental toward those with less evolved consciousness", "Difficulty with boundaries, wanting to help everyone", "May struggle with endings, completion, and letting go"],
        "career_guidance": "You excel in careers serving the greater good and creating positive change. Ideal roles include non-profit director, social activist, counselor, artist, musician, writer, healer, teacher, humanitarian aid worker, environmental advocate, or spiritual teacher. You thrive in purpose-driven organizations addressing global challenges. Consider careers in international development, human rights, environmental protection, or any field working toward systemic change. Your artistic abilities can be powerful vehicles for social commentary and transformation. Avoid purely profit-driven corporations or work that conflicts with your values. You need to feel your work contributes to making the world better. Your career satisfaction comes from knowing your efforts have helped people and advanced humanity's evolution, not from personal glory or wealth.",
        "relationship_guidance": "In relationships, you are deeply loving, accepting, and devoted to your partner's growth. Your challenge is maintaining healthy boundaries and not losing yourself in the relationship or trying to rescue your partner from their journey. You may attract wounded people who need healing, but be careful not to confuse love with codependency. Healthy relationships require partners who share your values and commitment to growth but don't need you to save them. You need someone who supports your humanitarian work while ensuring you don't sacrifice your well-being. Practice receiving love as freely as you give it—this is difficult for you because giving feels more natural. In friendships, you attract diverse people and serve as the compassionate listener everyone seeks. As a parent, you raise conscious, compassionate children but must balance idealism with practical life skills. Your greatest relationship growth comes from learning that you cannot heal everyone, and that sometimes love means allowing people to face their own lessons.",
        "financial_guidance": "Your financial challenge is valuing your own needs while serving others. You may give away money impulsively to causes or people in need, leaving yourself financially vulnerable. Your income potential varies depending on whether you monetize your gifts appropriately. Artists, writers, and healers can earn well if they overcome beliefs that spirituality and money don't mix. Build wealth by creating income streams aligned with your values—teaching, creating transformative content, consulting, or building social enterprises that do well by doing good. You benefit from having a financial advisor or partner who handles practical money management while you focus on service. Avoid financial martyrdom—you cannot serve effectively if you're struggling financially. Your prosperity grows when you understand that abundance allows you to serve more powerfully and that receiving supports the cycle of giving. Practice believing you deserve prosperity for the tremendous value you provide to the world.",
        "daily_practices": ["Morning meditation or spiritual practice to center yourself in divine love", "Energy protection rituals to avoid absorbing others' emotional pain", "Creative expression (art, music, writing) to process intense emotions", "Time in nature to ground your energy and reconnect with earth", "Regular check-in: Am I carrying burdens that aren't mine?", "Acts of self-compassion equal to the compassion you show others", "Conscious completion practice to honor endings as sacred"],
        "famous_examples": "Life Seal 9 individuals include humanitarian visionaries such as Mother Teresa (August 26), Mahatma Gandhi (October 2), and Bob Marley (February 6). These figures demonstrate the compassionate service, global consciousness, and transformative impact characteristic of Life Seal 9, dedicating their lives to uplifting humanity.",
        "spiritual_focus": "Centers on universal love and service to all, reflecting God's heart for the world. Your spiritual path involves learning that you are human too, not just a vessel for divine love. You are called to embody universal compassion while honoring your individual human needs. Your challenge is accepting that you cannot save everyone and that completion is part of the divine cycle—death gives way to rebirth. Practice releasing outcomes, trusting that your contribution is enough even when you cannot solve everything.",
        "bible_verses": "Micah 6:8 - 'He has shown you, O mortal, what is good. And what does the Lord require of you? To act justly and to love mercy and to walk humbly with your God.'; Matthew 25:40 - 'Truly I tell you, whatever you did for one of the least of these brothers and sisters of mine, you did for me.'; 1 John 4:7 - 'Dear friends, let us love one another, for love comes from God. Everyone who loves has been born of God and knows God.'",
        "practical_guidance": ["Ground idealism in concrete action—start where you are with what you have", "Protect your energy while contributing to causes that align with your values", "Practice discernment about which battles to fight—you cannot address everything", "Value yourself as much as you value serving others", "Honor endings as necessary for new beginnings rather than clinging to what needs to release"]
    }
}
